The paper deals with document image classification using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of transfer learning and ensembling techniques also suggests relevance to machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL). The paper also involves classification of text-based documents, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of image datasets and deep learning models could also relate to multimedia (cs.MM).
